.TH pman 1 "27 Mar 2018" "1.0" "pman man page"
.SH NAME
pman \- Personal man pages
.SH SYNOPSIS
pman [-l] [-e COMMAND] [-r COMMAND] [--set-full-name | -n NAME] [--set-email | -m EMAIL] [--no-set-email] [--no-set-full-name] [-h] [COMMAND]
.SH DESCRIPTION
pman is a personal man pages tool for the system administrator. Create and view your own personal man pages.
.SH OPTIONS
[COMMAND] specifies the personal manual page you wish to view.

	-e : edit the personal man page of a certain COMMAND via vim

	-l : list all the available personal man pages made

	-h : view help 

	-r : remove COMMAND from personal manual pages (irreversible)

	--set-full-name, -n : set the full NAME of the author. Use double quotes if the NAME contains spaces

	--set-email, -m : set the EMAIL of the author

	--no-set-name : remove the set name

	--no-set-email : remove the set email
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Anas Ayubi (anasayubi7152@gmail.com)
